From: Claude Fleet <fleet@factorylm.local>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 11:52:29 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): work-order history as citable evidence
 (flag-gated)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Atlas CMMS is deployed but the diagnostic path never read work-order
history as evidence (audit issue #10). Add shared/wo_evidence.py:
recall_work_orders() reads Hub NeonDB work_orders JOIN cmms_equipment
(the store hub_neon.py writes to; TEXT-family tenant_id, matched by
uns_path descendant or equipment_number ILIKE) via psycopg2 +
asyncio.to_thread — same pattern as ctx_enrichment.py.

Engine injects a citable WORK ORDER HISTORY block for the CONFIRMED
asset in _call_with_correction, next to the existing kg/live/ctx
blocks. Gated by ENABLE_WO_EVIDENCE (default OFF); any miss (no
tenant/asset, DB unreachable, timeout) returns "" — flag-off and
error paths are byte-for-byte unchanged. Offline tests mock the DB.
